[Student "S"]
{With 6 points, NORTH must respond to SOUTH's 1\C opening bid. 
While it is often correct to respond by bidding suits "up-the-line", NORTH should 
skip over the weak \D suit in favor of showing the 4-card 
Major \S suit.

SOUTH knows that NORTH may only have four \Ss, but with four of her own she can support the 
suit. Since she has a minimum opening bid she merely raises to 2\S. 
With his minimum response hand NORTH passes.}

